# Repomix workflow

Upstream: [yamadashy/repomix](https://github.com/yamadashy/repomix). CLI: **`npx repomix@latest`** from **this repository root**.

## Before code changes (required)

1. **Pick scope** — the smallest set of paths that covers **every** file you will add or edit in this change (typically `src/`, `tests/`, and/or `docs/requirements/` or a single domain under `docs/requirements/domains/`).
2. **Pack** — always pass **`-o`** under **`.repomix/`** with distinct filenames (avoid default output in the repo root):
   ```bash
   npx repomix@latest src -o .repomix/pack-src.xml
   npx repomix@latest tests -o .repomix/pack-tests.xml
   npx repomix@latest docs/requirements -o .repomix/pack-requirements.xml
   ```
   Per-domain packs and naming: **`.claude/skills/repomix/SKILL.md`** and **`docs/prompt/tools/repomix.md`**.
3. **Load** — **read** every pack that covers your scope **before** proposing or applying patches. Regenerate if the tree changed since the last read.

If **`src/`** or **`tests/`** do not exist yet, pack **`docs/requirements`** (and any directories that do exist) until those trees are added.

## Hygiene

- **`.repomix/`** must remain **gitignored** (local LLM context only).
- Repomix honors **`.gitignore`**; do not bypass ignores to include secrets.

## One-liner

**Pack edit scope into `.repomix/*.xml` → read those packs → edit. Pair with GitNexus gates (`gitnexus.mdc`).**
